msgid "Rotary knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Track selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Load buttons"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Loads currently highlighted track to the corresponding deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Pushing rotary knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid ""
"Push: Loads currently highlighted track to the preview deck and plays it. – "
"Release: jump to 30% position – Push again without rotary: Stop preview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + rotary knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Library section selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + pushing rotary knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "toggle expanding library section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:50
msgid "Switching between decks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:53
msgid ""
"Pressing Shift + “Key Lock / Tempo Range” allows the left deck to switch "
"between decks 1 and 3 and the right deck to switch between decks 2 and 4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:55
msgid "Volume, equalizers & filters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:58
msgid ""
"Between the decks the usual faders, crossfader and EQ knobs can be found. A "
"filter knob is also available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:60
msgid ""
"Knobs are available for the main and headphones level. These are functional "
"but are not reflected in Mixxx, as they control the controller’s soundcard "
"directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:62
msgid ""
"The filter fade button allows to use the crossfader in an innovative way "
"that fades across songs through filtering instead of fading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:64
msgid ""
"There is no trim/gain knob, but the same effect can be achieved by using the"
" filter knobs while holding shift."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:66
msgid "Jogwheels, tempo & vinyl mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:69
msgid ""
"When a deck is paused, the jogwheel allows you to browse through a track. If"
" you want to browse faster, hold shift while using the jogwheel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:71
msgid ""
"When a deck is playing, using the jogwheel allows you to temporarily change "
"the tempo of the playing track. Again, holding shift exaggerates this "
"effect."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:73
msgid ""
"The tempo slider allows changing the tempo of each deck. This normally "
"changes the pitch of a track, you can make the pitch stay constant by "
"pressing the “key lock / tempo range” button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:75
msgid ""
"Vinyl mode makes the jogwheels emulate the way turntables work. Vinyl mode "
"can be toggled by pressing the “vinyl / slip” button. Touching the outer "
"plastic ring of the jogwheel will make it behave as with vinyl mode off. "
"Touching the metal disc simulates touching the vinyl record, so just putting"
" your hand on it will stop the “vinyl”. You can scratch in a similar way as "
"with turntables in vinyl mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:79
msgid "Slip mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:82
msgid ""
"By pressing shift + “vinyl / slip” you can toggle slip mode. When entering "
"slip mode, Mixxx remembers what point exactly of the track should be playing"
" even if, for example, you scratch or make a loop. This allows to return to "
"the original pace of the track."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:85
msgid "Pads - lower row"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:88
msgid ""
"The play and cue pads should be self-explaining. The sync pad toggles sync "
"lock for a deck, which tries to beatmatch the deck with the others, and also"
" syncs the tempo between them, even when the tempo of one deck is changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:91
msgid "Additional functions can be accessed by holding shift"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + play"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Plays the track in reverse and enables slipping (see slip mode)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + cue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid ""
"Brakes the track as if the power of the motor on a turntable was turned off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid ""
"Enables quantize mode (this makes most actions, e.g. setting the cue point, "
"fall to the nearest beat)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:100
msgid "Pads - hot cue mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:103
msgid ""
"In hot cue mode the upper row of pads control the hotcues. Pressing a pad "
"that is not lit sets a hotcue. Pressing a pad that is lit makes the track "
"jump and play from that hotcue. Pressing a pad while holding shift deletes "
"that hotcue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:106
msgid ""
"You can control a set of 4 more hotcues by pressing shift + hot cue. The hot"
" cue button will start blinking. The pads will behave in the same way, but "
"controlling hotcues 5 to 8."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:108
msgid "Pads - auto loop mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:111
msgid ""
"Pressing the pads in auto loop mode will make loops of a specific length "
"measured in beats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Pad 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "1 beat loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Pad 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "2 beat loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Pad 3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "4 beat loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Pad 4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "8 beat loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + pad 1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "16 beat loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + pad 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "32 beat loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + pad 3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "64 beat loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:124
msgid "Pads - manual loop mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:127
msgid ""
"This mode will make the pads control looping in the way labeled on them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Set loop in"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Set loop out"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Toggles loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Halve loop length"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Shift + pad 4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Double loop length"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Move loop one beat backward"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:20
msgid "Move loop one beat forward"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:140
msgid "Pads - sampler mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:143
msgid ""
"In sampler mode the sampler can be controlled. To load a file into a "
"sampler, first press the sampler button while holding shift, so that the "
"sampler button starts blinking. Now pressing a pad will load the currently "
"highlighted track on the library into the corresponding sampler. Pressing a "
"pad while holding shift will eject the sample."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:146
msgid ""
"To play samples, press the sampler button without holding shift (it should "
"not blink). Pressing a pad will start playing the corresponding sample, "
"pressing a pad while holding shift will stop it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:148
msgid "Pads - loop roll (shift + auto loop)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/pioneer_ddj_sb.md:151
msgid ""
"By pressing the auto loop button while holding shift (it should start "
"blinking) you can make loop rolls. This mode combines auto loops with slip "
"mode. The pads will start a loop in the current position with a determinate "
"beat length while simultaneously enabling slip mode, so that when releasing "
"the pad the track will continue playing as if the loop never happened."
msgstr ""

